com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetMergeHistoryResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianResponse
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetMergeHistoryResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GetMergeHistoryResponse
extends SiperianResponse
    Response to a GetMergeHistoryRequest.

    The response contains one trust setting object for each column UID specified in the request, in the same order as the list of column UIDs in the request.

    The response contains the root node of the tree is the surviving rowid (see getHistoryTree()). The child nodes (see getChildNodes()) represent the records that have been merged into the surviving record. Each node contains the rowid and merge date of the record (see MergeHistoryNode).

    Usage Example:

    The following example shows how to print out the merge history in a GetMergeHistoryResponse:

    {   // ...
      GetMergeHistoryResponse response = (GetMergeHistoryResponse) sipClient.process(request);
      GetMergeHistoryResponse response = (GetMergeHistoryResponse) sipClient.process(request);
      MergeHistoryNode rootNode = response.getHistoryTree();
      printNode(rootNode, 0);
      //...
    }

    // ...

    //Helper method to iteratively print tree nodes.
    private void printNode(MergeHistoryNode node, int level)
    {
      
      ArrayList childNodes = node.getChildNodes();
      StringBuffer pad = new StringBuffer();
      for(int i=0; i < level; i++)
        pad.append(" ");
      for(int i; i < childNodes.size(); i++)
      {
        System.out.println(pad + "rowid="+node.getRowid() + ", merge date="+node.getMergeDate());
        printNode(node, level + 1);
      }
    }

    For more details, see GetMergeHistoryRequest.
